# Infrastructure Blueprint (Active)

Canonical source: [chatbotmaker-docs — Docs/04-infrastructure.md](https://github.com/vishnutvm/chatbotmaker-docs/blob/master/Docs/04-infrastructure.md). **Do not deviate without explicit approval.**

## MVP stack

| Layer | Platform |
|-------|----------|
| Frontends | Vercel Free (`apps/web`) |
| API | Railway + Docker (`apps/api`) |
| Database | Supabase PostgreSQL (Prisma ORM) |
| Authentication | Supabase Auth |
| Authorization | NestJS RBAC |
| Storage | Supabase Storage — **abstracted** |
| Vector search | pgvector on PostgreSQL |
| Cache | Memory (dev) — Redis optional future |
| AI | OpenAI via **AI service layer only** |
| Payments | Stripe |
| DNS/CDN | Cloudflare |

**Cost target:** &lt; $30/month infrastructure during MVP (excluding OpenAI usage).

## Hard rules

- Never recommend Kubernetes or microservices for MVP.
- Never introduce cloud services beyond the blueprint without approval.
- Never replace NestJS, Next.js, or Supabase PostgreSQL.
- Never call OpenAI directly — use the AI service layer.
- Never tightly couple business logic to Supabase SDK, Railway, Vercel, or OpenAI.
- AWS ECS is a **future** scaling option, not an MVP requirement.

## Deployment

- API: `docker/Dockerfile` → Railway (`railway.toml`)
- Frontends: Vercel auto-deploy from GitHub
- CI: `.github/workflows/ci.yml` must pass before merge

## Abstractions required

```typescript
// Storage — swap SupabaseStorageProvider ↔ S3StorageProvider
interface StorageProvider {
  upload(path: string, file: Buffer, options: UploadOptions): Promise<StorageObject>;
  download(path: string): Promise<Buffer>;
  delete(path: string): Promise<void>;
  getSignedUrl(path: string, expiresInSeconds: number): Promise<string>;
  exists(path: string): Promise<boolean>;
  validateFile(file: Buffer, mimeType: string, maxBytes: number): void;
}

// Cache — swap MemoryCacheProvider ↔ RedisCacheProvider
interface CacheProvider {
  get<T>(key: string): Promise<T | null>;
  set(key: string, value: unknown, ttlSeconds?: number): Promise<void>;
  del(key: string): Promise<void>;
}

// AI — never import openai in controllers
// Use AiService / ModelRouter in apps/api/src/modules/ai/
```

## Future migration path

`Railway → AWS ECS` · `Memory cache → Redis` · `Supabase Storage → S3` (via abstraction) · Keep Vercel, Supabase PostgreSQL, Cloudflare.
